 {"id": "franken_networkx-classpred", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] Graph.is_directed(None) raises \u2014 nx generators with create_using=fnx.Graph fail", "description": "nx.utils.misc.check_create_using does `G.is_directed(None) if isinstance(G, type) else G.is_directed()` when deciding whether a create_using CLASS matches expected directedness. On nx, these are plain methods that ignore self, so self=None works. fnx's Rust descriptors require a real instance and raise TypeError: 'descriptor is_directed for franken_networkx.Graph objects doesn't apply to a NoneType object'. This broke nx.gnp_random_graph, nx.barabasi_albert_graph, and any nx generator with create_using=fnx.Graph. Fix: _make_class_safe_predicate wraps is_directed / is_multigraph so class-level calls return the class-level default and instance calls still delegate to the Rust descriptor.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:13:35.291148Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: class-level is_directed/is_multigraph wrappers applied to all 4 graph classes. 6 regression tests in TestClassLevelPredicates cover class/instance paths + end-to-end nx generators with fnx create_using.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:13:35.291148Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:13:35.291148Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-rmvbunch", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] remove_edges_from/remove_nodes_from(gen_reading_self) hits \"Already mutably borrowed\"", "description": "nx internals call `g.remove_edges_from(nx.selfloop_edges(g))` and `g.remove_nodes_from(iterator_reading_g)` \u2014 e.g. nx.community.girvan_newman does exactly this. The Rust remove_*_from mutably borrows self while iterating the bunch; the generator's read of self._adj needs an immutable borrow and raises `RuntimeError: Already mutably borrowed`. Same class as br-addedgesgen \u2014 fix by materializing the bunch before the Rust call.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-9: _remove_bunch_materialized wrapper on Graph/DiGraph/MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph remove_edges_from and remove_nodes_from."}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-rustlag", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] minimum_cycle_basis symbol missing from .so (in-flight Rust rebuild)", "description": "A parallel agent added `from franken_networkx._fnx import minimum_cycle_basis` without a corresponding .so rebuild, breaking fnx import entirely. Hardened the import with try/except and fall back to the existing `_minimum_cycle_basis_via_parity` helper so the package stays loadable while the Rust side catches up.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-9: optional import with fallback to Python helper."}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-copycp", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] copy.copy(fnx_graph) does not share graph-level attrs (nx does)", "description": "In nx, `copy.copy(G)` produces a graph H where H.graph IS G.graph (same dict reference). In fnx, copy.copy(G) produces an independent graph with a separate .graph dict, so mutations to G.graph don't propagate to H.graph. This is arguably safer but diverges from nx's `copy.copy` contract. Users relying on nx's share-by-reference semantics in copy.copy will see different behavior on fnx. Fix requires overriding __copy__ at Python layer to preserve the dict reference for graph attrs (and potentially node/edge attrs too). Queued because fnx's deeper-copy semantics here are a deliberate design choice; making copy.copy share references requires careful thought about what else should be shared. Users who need nx's shallow semantics should use G.copy() (which on nx doesn't share either) or explicit view wrappers.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:33:45.271927Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:33:45.271927Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
